net.automatalib.serialization.automaton

Interface SimpleAutomatonDeserializer<S,I>

  • Type Parameters:
    S - The state type of the de-serialized hypothesis
    I - The default input symbol type
    All Superinterfaces:
    InputModelDeserializer<I,SimpleAutomaton<S,I>>, ModelDeserializer<InputModelData<I,SimpleAutomaton<S,I>>>
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    SimpleAutomatonSerializationProvider<S,I>

    public interface SimpleAutomatonDeserializer<S,I>
extends InputModelDeserializer<I,SimpleAutomaton<S,I>>
    A refining interface of InputModelDeserializer that binds the model to SimpleAutomatons. It also adds new functionality to read systems of arbitrary input type given a transform function from the default input type (specified by implementing class).

    Note: These model-specific interfaces may be omitted if Java starts supporting higher-kinded generics (or we switch to a language that supports these).

    Author:
    frohme
